		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That Castlevania III example is a really interesting one, especially since the corresponding VRC6 Akumajou Densetsu track has the extra channels to play a full chord there and doesn't need the arpeggios. It makes the arps seem like a last resort when trying to port the sound to the unexpanded NES audio.

		

		</td>
