	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I always thought the stock NES, aside from the Triangle Wave's lack of volume, was well suited for whatever you needed.  I never really liked the concept of sound expansion unless it was to add a new sound type, or to prevent sound effects from cutting the audio.  Most efforts I've seen with expanded audio are Famitracker songs that seem to use VRC6 just because.  Plus all of the best/memorable songs were conveniently written for the 2A03; Solstice theme (and any Follin soundtrack), Moon theme, Mario above ground theme, Sunsoft's music, Contra's music...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


